Following will be migrgated to latex in the future.
The text README file will be generated by latex source.


This branch of hobbitmon released by T.J. Yang with following differences


1. hobbit client and hobbit server has their own account and group IDs.
   1.1  account and group ids are added/removed upon package installation/removal.  
2. hobbbit client and server are packaged in TWW Hyper Package Manager
   format.
   - the TWW package format is native package format plus a xml file
   about packge in zip format.
3. Using the client.
   3.1 /etc/init.d/hobbitmonclient42 to start and stop hobbitmon.
   3.2 install hobbitmon will create hobbitmon accounts and groups
       in your local password and group files.
       ie, "/opt/bin/pkg-inst hobbitmon-client".
   3.3 remove hobbitmon package will remove the account and delete
       all the log files.
       ie, "/opt/bin/pkg-rm  hobbitmon-client".
4. Using makefile to automate the hobbitmon software compilation and
   pacakge creation.
 
5. Using doxygen and latex to automate the hobbitmon documenation efforts.

6. Use TWW's pkg-inst cross-platform package management utility.
   5.1  Install: 
   - You will be able to use "pkg-inst hobbit-client" to install
   hobbit client and its depended software.
   - "pkg-inst -N hobbit-client"
   - You can install a perticular version of hobbitmon  client by
   "pkg-inst hobbitmon-client-4.3.0"
   5.2 Removal:
   - "pkg-rm  hobbit-client"
   5.3 Query package information.
   -  "pkg-info hobbit-client"
6. Current supported OS are
   1. Solaris 2.6 to 2.11 sparc.
   2. Solaris 10 and 11 Intel.
   3. HP-UX 10.20 to 11.11
   4. RH Linux 9 to RH 4.

